I"“<p>If you want to add windows boot manager to grub, follow these steps;</p>

<p>1-Download <strong>os-prober</strong><br />
2-Run:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">sudo </span>os-prober</code></pre></figure>

<p>If there is an output like that, you are good to go:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">-&gt; <span class="nb">sudo </span>os-prober
/dev/nvme1n1p1@/EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi:Windows Boot Manager:Windows:efi</code></pre></figure>

<p><br />
3- Append this line, <strong>GRUB_DISABLE_OS_PROBER=false</strong>, to the <strong>/etc/default/grub</strong> file.<br />
4- Run:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">sudo </span>grub-mkconfig <span class="nt">-o</span> /boot/grub/grub.cfg</code></pre></figure>

<p><br />
Done !</p>
:ET